1. Theoretical models                                             7025 1451
 The POD code is based on the spherical optical model, the        7025 1451
distorted-wave Born approximaiton (DWBA), one-component exciton   7025 1451
preequilibrium model, and the Hauser-Feshbach-Moldauer statis-    7025 1451
tical model.  With the preequilibrium model, semi-empirical       7025 1451
pickup and knockout process can be taken into account for         7025 1451
composite-particle emission.  The gamma-ray emission from the     7025 1451
compound nucleus can be calculated within the framework of the    7025 1451
exciton model.  The code is capable of reading in particle        7025 1451
transmission coefficients calculated by separate spherical or     7025 1451
coupled-channel optical model code. In this evaluation, the OPTMAN7025 1451
/4/ code was employed for neutrons, while the ECIS code           7025 1451
/5/ was adopted for charged particles.                            7025 1451
                                                                  7025 1451
